  "top10": {
    "introHtml": "<p>Ranked for a cheap, fun second car \u2014 condition and reliability over raw miles. Chrome browser was unavailable for this run; Cars.com was blocked by bot protection and CarGurus distance filter required JS. AutoTrader returned 77 properly distance-filtered local listings (page 1 of ~4 shown). Top 10 drawn primarily from AutoTrader local results plus one CarGurus Springfield NJ listing.</p>",
    "picks": [
      {
        "rank": 1,
        "year": 2001,
        "make": "Toyota",
        "model": "MR2",
        "trim": "Spyder",
        "price": 9250,
        "mileage": 74000,
        "location": "Haverford, PA",
        "distanceMi": 18.11,
        "dealer": "Private Seller Exchange",
        "source": "autotrader",
        "url": "https://www.autotrader.com/cars-for-sale/vehicle/781215886",
        "dealRating": null,
        "imageUrl": "https://images2.autotrader.com/ps-vehicle-media/e8647d59-9f2a-4c15-b142-6e6f089704a4.jpg",
        "whyGood": "Mid-engine, rear-wheel-drive, 74K miles with clean history \u2014 the MR2 Spyder is one of the most entertaining convertibles ever made. The 1ZZ-FE is bulletproof; 74K is nothing on this engine. No Accidents reported, Private Seller (avoid dealer markup). At $9,250 for a mid-engine drop-top this close, this is the best pure fun-per-dollar on the list.",
        "whatToVerify": "Check for rear-cradle rust (common in salt states). Operate top fully. Inspect clutch feel \u2014 worn clutch is common at this age. Check for frame/body seam cracks near rear towers. Verify 5-speed shifts crisply through all gears. Ensure AC compressor is functional (easy to delete on MR2). Look for wet carpet behind seats indicating windshield seal leak.",
        "bottomLine": "The top pick: mid-engine fun at under $10K, close-by, low miles, clean history."
      },
      {
        "rank": 2,
        "year": 2004,
        "make": "BMW",
        "model": "330Ci",
        "trim": "Convertible",
        "price": 10500,
        "mileage": 88000,
        "location": "Newtown Square, PA",
        "distanceMi": 13.18,
        "dealer": "Private Seller Exchange",
        "source": "autotrader",
        "url": "https://www.autotrader.com/cars-for-sale/vehicle/781514334",
        "dealRating": null,
        "imageUrl": "https://images2.autotrader.com/ps-vehicle-media/6e7e21d8-082f-45a2-a1af-895c29de3db9.jpg",
        "whyGood": "E46 330Ci is the gold standard affordable European sports convertible. The M54 3.0L inline-6 is smooth, reliable, and a joy to rev. Only 88K miles with No Accidents, 13 miles away in Newtown Square PA. Clean title via Private Seller Exchange. E46 convertible market has bottomed \u2014 this is the bottom of the appreciation curve.",
        "whatToVerify": "Operate hydraulic top through full cycle (listen for pump whine, check for torn top fabric and yellowed rear window). Check DISA valve (rattling on cold start), cooling system hoses and expansion tank (brittle at age), oil leaks from valve cover and rear main seal, CCV system. Check subframe rear mounting points for rust/cracks \u2014 critical on E46. Test all electronics including convertible switches.",
        "bottomLine": "Best-rounded buy: German sports convertible, low miles, close-by, clean history \u2014 the E46 is a keeper."
      },
      {
        "rank": 3,
        "year": 2007,
        "make": "Pontiac",
        "model": "Solstice",
        "trim": "GXP",
        "price": 10995,
        "mileage": 51000,
        "location": "Sewell, NJ",
        "distanceMi": 25.07,
        "dealer": "Automotive Avenues of Sewell",
        "source": "autotrader",
        "url": "https://www.autotrader.com/cars-for-sale/vehicle/780313347",
        "dealRating": null,
        "imageUrl": "https://images2.autotrader.com/hn/c/d19900ee931449df8b7e42258c60ab2b.jpg",
        "whyGood": "The GXP trim is the one to get: 260hp turbocharged Ecotec 2.0L, vastly more fun than the base 177hp Solstice. Only 51K miles is exceptional for a 2007. These are appreciating \u2014 Kappa-platform Solstice/Sky GXPs have a cult following. Manual (5-speed) or automatic: check listing detail for transmission.",
        "whatToVerify": "Confirm transmission is manual (GXP purists prefer it). Check for oil leaks around turbo oil feed and return lines. Test top operation \u2014 the Solstice soft top can develop leaks at the rear corners. Check door seals carefully. Look for rust along lower rocker panels and door bottoms. Inspect intercooler for damage. GXP-specific: check for boost solenoid codes.",
        "bottomLine": "Turbo fun at 51K miles \u2014 the GXP is the correct Solstice to buy and this one has barely been used."
      },
      {
        "rank": 4,
        "year": 2000,
        "make": "BMW",
        "model": "Z3",
        "trim": "2.8",
        "price": 7940,
        "mileage": 75000,
        "location": "Haverford, PA",
        "distanceMi": 14.81,
        "dealer": "Private Seller Exchange",
        "source": "autotrader",
        "url": "https://www.autotrader.com/cars-for-sale/vehicle/775917821",
        "dealRating": null,
        "imageUrl": "https://images2.autotrader.com/ps-vehicle-media/c729256c-6312-44de-8d87-e2936f437cb1.jpeg",
        "whyGood": "2.8L M52TU inline-6 is the sweet spot of Z3 engines: enough power to be fun, none of the complexity of the M roadster. Under $8K with No Accidents and Clean Title is hard to beat for a German roadster at 75K miles. Only 15 miles away. Z3 maintenance is straightforward and parts are plentiful.",
        "whatToVerify": "Operate soft top fully. Check plastic rear window for cloudiness/cracks. Inspect underbody rocker panels for rust \u2014 Z3s can rust on the inner sills. Check cooling system expansion tank (brittle), oil leaks (expected at age), transmission fluid color. Test VANOS operation (cold-start rattle is normal if brief). Verify power windows cycle smoothly.",
        "bottomLine": "Best bang-for-buck roadster on the list \u2014 a well-kept 2.8 Z3 is nearly unbeatable for under $8K."
      },
      {
        "rank": 5,
        "year": 2001,
        "make": "BMW",
        "model": "325Ci",
        "trim": "Convertible",
        "price": 10000,
        "mileage": 60000,
        "location": "Ardmore, PA",
        "distanceMi": 15.42,
        "dealer": "Mancini Motors",
        "source": "autotrader",
        "url": "https://www.autotrader.com/cars-for-sale/vehicle/778490100",
        "dealRating": null,
        "imageUrl": "https://images2.autotrader.com/hn/c/b66fbee21a2f4330a0f4ac16fbfdc4bf.jpg",
        "whyGood": "E46 325Ci with only 60K miles is extremely low for a 2001. No Accidents, clean history, a proper dealer in Ardmore PA. 2.5L M54 is bulletproof. The E46 convertible has a genuine back seat (unlike Z3), making it the more practical fun car. $10K for 60K miles on an E46 is fair market.",
        "whatToVerify": "Same E46 checks as the 330Ci: hydraulic top operation, subframe mounting rust (critical \u2014 look underneath), DISA valve rattle, CCV system, cooling system hoses and tank. Also check for service records \u2014 at 60K miles, timing chain guide and VANOS should have been inspected. Test all 4 windows.",
        "bottomLine": "Lowest-mileage E46 on the list and within 16 miles \u2014 a compelling pick if the subframe checks out."
      },
      {
        "rank": 6,
        "year": 2010,
        "make": "BMW",
        "model": "328i",
        "trim": "Convertible",
        "price": 10499,
        "mileage": 80000,
        "location": "Haverford, PA",
        "distanceMi": 14.81,
        "dealer": "Private Seller Exchange",
        "source": "autotrader",
        "url": "https://www.autotrader.com/cars-for-sale/vehicle/781593445",
        "dealRating": null,
        "imageUrl": "https://images2.autotrader.com/ps-vehicle-media/fd292d83-9f89-4a33-9102-644a8c3af9b5.jpg",
        "whyGood": "E93 328i convertible (hardtop retractable) at 80K miles \u2014 more modern than the E46, with a full steel folding hardtop that seals better and looks cleaner than a soft top. N52 engine is generally reliable. Clean title, Private Seller Exchange. 15 miles away in Haverford.",
        "whatToVerify": "Retractable hardtop has many motors/sensors \u2014 cycle it 5+ times and listen for hesitation or grinding. Check for E93-specific water ingress behind rear seats (top seal failure). Inspect N52 for valve cover oil leaks (common). Check electric water pump status \u2014 failure is common and can strand you. Test all DSC/traction control electronics.",
        "bottomLine": "More modern and weather-sealed than a soft top \u2014 if the folding hardtop mechanism checks out, this is a great daily-drivable convertible."
      },
      {
        "rank": 7,
        "year": 2012,
        "make": "MINI",
        "model": "Cooper",
        "trim": "S",
        "price": 9400,
        "mileage": 98000,
        "location": "Haverford, PA",
        "distanceMi": 16.79,
        "dealer": "Private Seller Exchange",
        "source": "autotrader",
        "url": "https://www.autotrader.com/cars-for-sale/vehicle/777472503",
        "dealRating": null,
        "imageUrl": "https://images2.autotrader.com/ps-vehicle-media/3794377d-adea-46b7-93da-26eb2b3f4466.jpeg",
        "whyGood": "MINI Cooper S Convertible at 98K is still mid-life for this engine. The S has the 1.6T (N18 in 2012 \u2014 improved over previous N14/Prince engine). No Accidents, Clean Title. 17 miles away. MINIs are fun small convertibles, quick through corners, and parts are widely available.",
        "whatToVerify": "Check timing chain tensioner (N18 improved but still inspect). Look for coolant leaks around thermostat housing. Test soft top full cycle. Inspect for water intrusion in footwells (common MINI soft-top issue). Check for P0420 codes (catalytic converter). Verify all DSC and run-flat tire pressure monitoring works.",
        "bottomLine": "Peppy, fun, close-by, and priced right \u2014 a well-maintained S Convertible punches above its size."
      },
      {
        "rank": 8,
        "year": 2019,
        "make": "FIAT",
        "model": "124 Spider",
        "trim": "Lusso",
        "price": 14350,
        "mileage": 75827,
        "location": "Springfield, NJ",
        "distanceMi": 30,
        "dealer": "Dealer",
        "source": "cargurus",
        "url": "https://www.cargurus.com/details/429337423",
        "dealRating": "Great Deal",
        "imageUrl": null,
        "whyGood": "Mazda MX-5 Miata platform underneath a more stylish Italian body \u2014 shares the reliable 2.0L SkyActiv-G engine and suspension with the ND Miata. Lusso trim adds leather and Bose audio. 75K miles, Great Deal rating, and about 30 miles from Media in Springfield NJ. $14,350 is toward budget ceiling but CarGurus rates it a Great Deal.",
        "whatToVerify": "Same as any ND Miata: soft top operation and rear window clarity, door seal condition, check for rust at front frame rail (early ND issue, largely fixed by 2019). Verify Abarth turbo was not installed (some owners swap \u2014 not a factory Lusso feature). Test Bose audio. 124 Spider-specific: check turbocharger wastegate rattle if it has the Abarth 1.4T (Lusso is N/A, so confirm engine).",
        "bottomLine": "Great Deal on a Miata-platform roadster with Italian flair \u2014 the most modern car on this list and the only CarGurus local pick."
      },
      {
        "rank": 9,
        "year": 1997,
        "make": "BMW",
        "model": "Z3",
        "trim": "1.9",
        "price": 9995,
        "mileage": 69000,
        "location": "Media, PA",
        "distanceMi": 9.44,
        "dealer": "Dougherty Automotive Services",
        "source": "autotrader",
        "url": "https://www.autotrader.com/cars-for-sale/vehicle/781004495",
        "dealRating": null,
        "imageUrl": "https://images2.autotrader.com/hn/c/c480d9ba461344948a3357a5ee3d9a0e.jpg",
        "whyGood": "9.44 miles away \u2014 the closest car on the list. 69K miles. No Accidents. The 1.9 (M43 4-cylinder) is slow by modern standards but utterly reliable. $9,995 is a slight premium for a 1.9 vs a 2.8, but the low miles and proximity matter. Good beginner roadster, no major surprises.",
        "whatToVerify": "Same Z3 checks: top operation, rear window condition, rocker rust, cooling expansion tank, window regulators. The M43 is simple and robust \u2014 main thing to check is timing chain (listen for cold rattle). Verify odometer: 69K on a 1997 is plausible but confirm service history. Check for any aftermarket modifications.",
        "bottomLine": "Closest car on the list, low miles, dead-simple engine \u2014 great pick if you want easy ownership and minimal commute to pick it up."
      },
      {
        "rank": 10,
        "year": 2007,
        "make": "MINI",
        "model": "Cooper",
        "trim": "S",
        "price": 9500,
        "mileage": 65000,
        "location": "Lumberton, NJ",
        "distanceMi": 28.99,
        "dealer": "Josie's Auto Sales",
        "source": "autotrader",
        "url": "https://www.autotrader.com/cars-for-sale/vehicle/778854923",
        "dealRating": null,
        "imageUrl": "https://images2.autotrader.com/hn/c/938a412733d64cb88c70012dc1d8d4a5.jpg",
        "whyGood": "65K miles on a 2007 MINI S is genuinely low \u2014 these often have 150K+ by now. No Accidents. The 2007 used the R52 generation with the supercharged 1.6L (stronger than the turbocharged later cars in some ways). Fun, affordable, local. $9,500 for a 65K-mile S is reasonable.",
        "whatToVerify": "2007 uses the supercharged 1.6L (Tritec/Eaton SC) \u2014 check supercharger coupler (rubber coupling degrades, around $150 fix but causes drivability issues). Check timing chain tensioner noise on cold start. Inspect soft top seals carefully. Test power windows and convertible latches. Verify coolant level and look for signs of head gasket seepage.",
        "bottomLine": "Surprisingly low miles for its age and a fun driver \u2014 verify the SC coupler and top condition before buying."
      }
