        "whyGood": "1995 SN-95 Mustang GT with only 55K miles and No Accidents \u2014 extremely low for a 31-year-old pony car. The 5.0L HO V8 (last year of the Fox-era 5.0 in the SN-95 body) makes 215hp and sounds iconic with an aftermarket exhaust. At $10,495 with this mileage and a clean history, this is the only local Mustang surfaced. Manual (5-speed T-5 if so configured) would be ideal.",
        "whatToVerify": "SN-95 convertible: check convertible top mount-to-rocker welds for rust (known weakness on SN-95 ragtops \u2014 run your hand inside the rear quarter seam). Frame rails under the engine bay for rust. Confirm T-5 (if manual) shifts into all gears cleanly \u2014 3rd gear synchro. Check rear 7.5-inch axle (not the 8.8) for clunk on takeoff. Inspect timing chain rattle on cold start. Check for water stains on rear seat from top seal failure. Verify A/C operation.",
        "bottomLine": "The only local Mustang found \u2014 55K miles on an SN-95 GT is a rare find; check the top mounts and rocker rust before buying."
